\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 5.3 Exception Handling\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 Domain exceptions are defined inside the domain layer.\
Examples:\
\'95 AccountNotFoundException\uc0\u8232 \'95 CategoryNotFoundException\u8232 \'95 TransactionNotFoundException\
The REST layer converts them into HTTP responses using:\

\f0\b GlobalExceptionHandler
\f1\b0 \
This keeps the domain independent from HTTP concerns.\
