\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 5.9 Report Content Placeholder Strategy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 While JasperReports integration is not yet fully implemented, the report PDF content is temporarily stored as an empty byte array.\
Implementation decision:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 \
ReportPersistenceAdapter.save()\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 sets\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 \
byte[0]\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 as a placeholder value for the content field.\
This ensures the 
\f0\b NOT NULL constraint
\f1\b0  defined in the reports table is respected without breaking the report generation flow.\
Benefits:\
\'95 keeps the database schema stable\uc0\u8232 \'95 avoids nullable binary columns\u8232 \'95 allows report metadata to be persisted before PDF generation is implemented\u8232 \'95 maintains forward compatibility with the future JasperReports integration\

\f0\b JasperReports integration is partially implemented. The JasperReportAdapter exists and implements ReportGeneratorPort, but the .jrxml templates need to be regenerated in JasperReports 7.x format using Jaspersoft Studio 7. ReportControllerTest is disabled pending this fix.
